        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer556204747" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14795407845729262076">One of my all-time favorites! Long before the movie existed, I stumbled across this book in my college bookstore. This cover spoke to my YA fairy-tale-loving heart:<br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1534111106i/26118585.jpg' width='236' height='375' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>So I bought it, without knowing a thing about the story. And the book was NOT what I was expecting. <br/><br/>It was way, WAY better.<br/><br/>If you love the movie, read the book ... and don&apos;t let yourself get bogged down in the long, offbeat intro. (Skim it if you need to.) You&apos;ll get a lot of background history on the various characters, which can be </span>
  <span id="freeText14795407845729262076" style="display:none">One of my all-time favorites! Long before the movie existed, I stumbled across this book in my college bookstore. This cover spoke to my YA fairy-tale-loving heart:<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1534111106i/26118585.jpg" width="236" height="375" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>So I bought it, without knowing a thing about the story. And the book was NOT what I was expecting. <br><br>It was way, WAY better.<br><br>If you love the movie, read the book ... and don't let yourself get bogged down in the long, offbeat intro. (Skim it if you need to.) You'll get a lot of background history on the various characters, which can be extremely funny, and a little poignant. The movie is in large part very true to the book, but William Goldman has a dry, satirical sense of humor that doesn't entirely come through in the movie. (The part about the Greatest Kisses Ever cracks me up every time.)<br><br>But it's still about "Beasts of all natures and descriptions. Pain. Death. Brave men. Coward men. Strongest men. Chases. Escapes. Lies. Truths. Passions."<br><br>And it's wonderful.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14795407845729262076" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


